name: Flat bench press
description: Flat benches put more emphasis on the lower pecs, while incline benches put more emphasis on the upper pec, clavicular head and deltoids.

name: Inclined press
description: This workout is great for those who are looking to build strength, muscle mass and endurance in their chest and triceps

name: Decline press
description: The decline bench press targets your lower pectoral muscles. It's performed on a bench that's set to 15 to 30 degrees on a decline.

name: Cable flyes
description: Cable flyes are one of the best exercises for improving shoulder stability. It's also important to ensure that all other muscles around the shoulder area are activated properly too.

name: Shoulder press machine
description: Using the machine instead of the free weights helps you to isolate the deltoid muscles

name: Front raise
description: Front dumbbell raises are a great way to build upper-body strength, improve shoulder mobility and stability, and prevent injury

name: Lateral raise
description: Lateral raises add width and definition to your shoulder area if done consistently and correctly

name: Landmine Shoulder
description: The landmine press can be extremely beneficial to help build more lean muscle mass and strength in the shoulders.

name: Lat pulldown
description: The lat pulldown works the latissimus dorsi, the largest muscle in the back, as well as your biceps, rear delts, rhomboids and traps.

name: Bent-over row

name: Pull-ups
description: The pullup is one of the most effective exercises for strengthening the back muscles.

name: Deadlifts
description: The effects of deadlifts are evidence-based, with several case studies supporting its benefits on strength training.

name: Back squat
description: n addition to the lower body, the squat also targets your core muscles. These muscles include the rectus abdominis, obliques, transverse abdominis, and erector spinae.

name: Front squat
description: Like with back squats, front squats increase muscle mass in the lower body. The front squat muscles worked primarily include the quadriceps (quads), glutes, hips, and hamstrings.

name: Leg press
description: The leg press is the most important exercise in a workout. Regularly training with the leg press leads to strength and muscle gains in the largest muscles of the body

name: Bulgarian split squat
description: Bulgarian split squats are one of the best exercises to improve your squat. They will improve your balance, strength and coordination.
